Houston Geomarkers Project¶

The purpose of this notebook is to make a map of all of the pharmacies in Houston, as a first step to find where the Pharmacy Deserts are.

The first step is to get a Google API key here: https://developers.google.com/places/web-service/get-api-key

Houston longitude and latitude: 29.7604° N, 95.3698° W

More info here: https://developers.google.com/places/web-service/search

#Function to use Google Places Text Search to find names, addresses, and locations (latitude, longitude)

def get_locations(api_key, url, query, placetype = "pharmacy", next_page = "", count = 1):
    import requests, json
    
    if count == 1:
        r = requests.get(url + 'query=' + query +
                                 '&type=' + placetype +
                                 '&page_token=' + next_page +
                                 '&key=' + api_key) 
    elif (count > 1) and (next_page != ""):
        r = requests.get(url + 'query=' + query + '&page_token=' + next_page + '&key=' + api_key) 

    data = r.json() 
    results = data['results'] 

    # Lists to catch all the data
    name, address, lat, lng = [],[],[],[]

    # keep looping upto lenght of results 
    for i in range(len(results)):
        name.append(results[i]['name'])
        address.append(results[i]['formatted_address'])
        lat.append(results[i]['geometry']['location']['lat'])
        lng.append(results[i]['geometry']['location']['lng'])
        #print("{} at {}".format(name[i], address[i]))

    df = pd.DataFrame(data = {"Name":name, "Address":address, "Latitude":lat, "Longitude":lng})
    
    try:
        if data['next_page_token'] != "":
            return df, data['next_page_token']
    except:
        return df, " "

for i in range(len(zipcodes.Zipcode)):

    if i == 0:

#Data Cleaning

#Removing all entries for individual pharmacists (PharmD)
pharms["Keep"] = True
pharms["Coordinates"] = pharms.Latitude.astype(str) + ", " + pharms.Longitude.astype(str)

for i in range(len(pharms.Name)):
    if "PharmD" in pharms.Name[i]:
        pharms.at[i, "Keep"] = False
    if "RPH" in pharms.Name[i]:
        pharms.at[i, "Keep"] = False
    if "RPh" in pharms.Name[i]:
        pharms.at[i, "Keep"] = False
    if ", Pharm" in pharms.Name[i]:
        pharms.at[i, "Keep"] = False         
pharms.drop(pharms[pharms.Keep == False].index, inplace = True)
pharms.drop_duplicates(subset = "Coordinates")
pharms.reset_index(drop = True, inplace = True)

# Creating a Zipcodes column and filling in missing zipcodes with zipcodes from the nearest location based on lat, lng
pharms["Zipcodes"] = 0
for i in range(len(pharms.Zipcodes)):
    if pharms.Address[i][-10:-5].isdigit():
        pharms.at[i, "Zipcodes"] = pharms.Address[i][-10:-5]
        
pharms.sort_values(by = ["Latitude", "Longitude"], inplace = True)
pharms.reset_index(drop = True, inplace = True)
for i in range(len(pharms.Zipcodes)):
    if pharms.Zipcodes[i] == 0:
        pharms.at[i, "Zipcodes"] = pharms.Zipcodes[(i-1)]
In [79]:
#Creates a feature group for the map
def feature_group(df, name, colors, radius = 1609):
    import folium
    
    places = df.copy()
    feature_group = FeatureGroup(name=name)
    
    # for each row in the data, add a cicle marker
    for index, row in places.iterrows():              
        # add marker to the map
        feature_group.add_child(folium.Circle(location=(row["Latitude"],
                                        row["Longitude"]),
                                        radius=radius,
                                        color=colors,
                                        fill=True))            
    return feature_group

#Creating the map with multiple layers

import folium
from folium.map import *

# generate a map of Houston
geolocator = Nominatim(user_agent="Houston_Geomarkers")
location = geolocator.geocode("Houston, TX")
folium_map = folium.Map(location=[location.latitude, location.longitude],
                        zoom_start=11,
                        tiles="CartoDB positron",
                        width='100%')

#Decide on colors for the various markers
colors = ["#F34526","#FFD735","#3551FF","#35EAFF","#6DF326"]

#Create different map feature groups for each park type
folium_map.add_child(feature_group(df = pharms, name = "Pharmacies", colors = colors[2]))
folium_map.add_child(folium.map.LayerControl())

# Saving the map to an html file
outfp = "Houston_pharmacies_map.html"
folium_map.save(outfp)

#Houston Income from http://zipatlas.com/us/tx/houston/zip-code-comparison/median-household-income.htm

#Import csv of median household income by zipcode
income = pd.read_csv('HoustonIncome.csv', skiprows = 0, encoding='cp1252') 

#Create bins for income and assign a color scale value per bin
income['Bin'] = (pd.cut(income['Avg. Income/H/hold'], 
                          bins = [10000,20000,40000,60000,80000,100000,200000], 
                          labels = [10000,20000,40000,60000,80000,100000]))
income['Color'] = (pd.cut(income['Avg. Income/H/hold'], 
                          bins = [10000,20000,40000,60000,80000,100000,200000], 
                          labels = ['#4900FF','#8900FF', '#C800FF', '#FF00F6', '#FF00B6', '#FF0076']))
income.drop(axis = 1, labels = ['Location','City','Population','Avg. Income/H/hold'], inplace = True)

# Combine the income bins and colors with the original pharms dataframe
combo = pd.merge(left = pharms, right = income, how = "inner", left_on = pharms.Zipcodes, right_on = income['Zip Code'])
combo.drop(axis = 1, labels = ['key_0','Keep','Coordinates','Zip Code'], inplace = True)

#Creates a feature group for the map
def feature_group2(df, name, radius = 1609):
    import folium
    
    places = df.copy()
    feature_group = FeatureGroup(name=name)
    
    # for each row in the data, add a cicle marker
    for index, row in places.iterrows():              
        # add marker to the map
        feature_group.add_child(folium.Circle(location=(row["Latitude"],
                                        row["Longitude"]),
                                        radius=radius,
                                        color=row['Color'],
                                        fill=True))            
    return feature_group

#Create a draggable legend for the map
#Solution adapted from http://nbviewer.jupyter.org/gist/talbertc-usgs/18f8901fc98f109f2b71156cf3ac81cd

from branca.element import Template, MacroElement

template = """
{% macro html(this, kwargs) %}

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>jQuery UI Draggable - Default functionality</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="//code.jquery.com/ui/1.12.1/themes/base/jquery-ui.css">

  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.12.4.js"></script>
  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/ui/1.12.1/jquery-ui.js"></script>
  
  <script>
  $( function() {
    $( "#maplegend" ).draggable({
                    start: function (event, ui) {
                        $(this).css({
                            right: "auto",
                            top: "auto",
                            bottom: "auto"
                        });
                    }
                });
});

  </script>
</head>
<body>

 
<div id='maplegend' class='maplegend' 
    style='position: absolute; z-index:9999; border:2px solid grey; background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
     border-radius:6px; padding: 10px; font-size:16px; right: 20px; bottom: 20px;'>
     
<div class='legend-title'>Houston Pharmacies</div>
<div class='legend-scale'>
  <ul class='legend-labels'>
    <li><span style='background:#4900FF;opacity:0.7;'></span>$0 - $10k</li>
    <li><span style='background:#8900FF;opacity:0.7;'></span>$20k - $40k</li>
    <li><span style='background:#C800FF;opacity:0.7;'></span>$40k - $60k</li>
    <li><span style='background:#FF00F6;opacity:0.7;'></span>$60k - $80k</li>
    <li><span style='background:#FF00B6;opacity:0.7;'></span>$80k - $100k</li>
    <li><span style='background:#FF0076;opacity:0.7;'></span>$100k+</li>
<div class = 'legend-footer'>By median income by zip</div>

    
  </ul>
</div>
</div>
 
</body>
</html>

<style type='text/css'>
  .maplegend .legend-title {
    text-align: left;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 90%;
    }
  .maplegend .legend-footer {
    text-align: left;
    margin-top: 5px;
    margin-bottom: 0px;
    font-size: 50%;
    }
  .maplegend .legend-scale ul {
    margin: 0;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
    padding: 0;
    float: left;
    list-style: none;
    }
  .maplegend .legend-scale ul li {
    font-size: 80%;
    list-style: none;
    margin-left: 0;
    line-height: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
    }
  .maplegend ul.legend-labels li span {
    display: block;
    float: left;
    height: 16px;
    width: 30px;
    margin-right: 5px;
    margin-left: 0;
    border: 1px solid #999;
    }
  .maplegend .legend-source {
    font-size: 80%;
    color: #777;
    clear: both;
    }
  .maplegend a {
    color: #777;
    }
</style>
{% endmacro %}"""

macro = MacroElement()
macro._template = Template(template)

folium_map.get_root().add_child(macro)

# Saving the map to an html file
outfp = "Houston_pharmacies_map_by_income.html"
